'''達雷爾·伊薩'''（Darrell Issa；{{bd|1953年|11月1日}}）是[[美國|美國]]的一位政治人物，其家族擁有[[黎巴嫩|黎巴嫩]]、[[德國|德國]]及[[波西米亞|波西米亞]]多重血統，在2006年時也是[[美國國會|美國國會]]四位[[阿拉伯裔美國人|阿拉伯裔]]議員之一<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dBOF8Q685mAC&q=Charles+Boustany+lebanon&pg=PA775|title=Congressional Record, V. 152, Pt. 14, September 2006|first=U. S.|last=Congress|date=October 28, 2010|publisher=Government Printing Office|isbn=9780160867804|access-date=November 12, 2016|via=Google Books|archive-date=2022-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126173145/https://books.google.com/books?id=dBOF8Q685mAC&q=Charles+Boustany+lebanon&pg=PA775|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2013年至2019年間，他是加利福尼亞州第49選舉區選出的美國眾議員<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wedrawthelines.ca.gov/downloads/meeting_handouts_082011/map_20110815_ap_cd_49_certified.pdf|title=District 49|date=August 2011|work=California Redistricting Commission certified map|publisher=Healthy City|accessdate=January 5, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130325070703/http://wedrawthelines.ca.gov/downloads/meeting_handouts_082011/map_20110815_ap_cd_49_certified.pdf|archive-date=2013-03-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。他的黨籍是[[共和黨_(美國)|共和黨]]。伊薩曾經是一位商人。2013年，伊薩的總財產達3.55億美元，使他成為美國最富有的眾議員<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thehill.com/business-a-lobbying/317429-the-hills-50-wealthiest-lawmakers-?start=1|accessdate=September 30, 2013|title=Issa tops The Hill's 50 Wealthiest|publisher=TheHill.com|date=September 30, 2013|author=Ruyle, Megan|archive-date=2013-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130824151040/http://thehill.com/business-a-lobbying/317429-the-hills-50-wealthiest-lawmakers-?start=1|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Hall, Matthew T. (August 20, 2013). [http://utsandiego.com/news/2013/aug/20/issa-wealthiest-member-congress "Issa now wealthiest member of Congress"] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20140222024322/http://utsandiego.com/news/2013/aug/20/issa-wealthiest-member-congress |date=2014-02-22 }}. UTSanDiego.com.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2014/09/how-did-members-of-congress-get-so-wealthy/379848/|title=How Did Members of Congress Get So Wealthy?|last=Gordon|first=Noah|date=September 9, 2014|work=The Atlantic|accessdate=September 9, 2014|archive-date=2021-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227041432/https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2014/09/how-did-members-of-congress-get-so-wealthy/379848/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

達雷爾·伊薩生於[[俄亥俄州|俄亥俄州]][[克里夫蘭|克里夫蘭]]，父母分別為威廉和瑪莎·伊薩<ref>{{cite news|author=Leduff, Charlie|date=July 23, 2003|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/07/23/us/california-recall-backer-feels-heat.html|title=California Recall Backer Feels Heat|work=Nytimes.com|access-date=September 30, 2013|archive-date=2022-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126173627/https://www.nytimes.com/2003/07/23/us/california-recall-backer-feels-heat.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/158119841.html?dids=158119841:158119841&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Sep+01%2C+2002&author=FAYE+FIORE&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=The+Rock%2C+the+Hard+Place+and+the+Man+in+the+Middle%3B+As+'an+Arab+American+Who+Grew+Up+Delivering+Poultry+for+a+Rabbi%2C'+San+Diego-+Area+Congressman+Darrell+Issa+Is+Facing+a+Telling+Post-Sept.+11+Political+Dilemma%3A+'So+Who+Am+I%3F'&pqatl=google|title=Los Angeles Times: The Rock, the Hard Place and the Man in the Middle|publisher=Pqasb.pqarchiver.com|date=September 1, 2002|access-date=September 30, 2013|url-access=subscription|archive-date=2013-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130325070718/http://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/158119841.html?dids=158119841%3A158119841&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS%3AFT&type=current&date=Sep%2001%2C%202002&author=FAYE%20FIORE&pub=Los%20Angeles%20Times&desc=The%20Rock%2C%20the%20Hard%20Place%20and%20the%20Man%20in%20the%20Middle%3B%20As%20%27an%20Arab%20American%20Who%20Grew%20Up%20Delivering%20Poultry%20for%20a%20Rabbi%2C%27%20San%20Diego-%20Area%20Congressman%20Darrell%20Issa%20Is%20Facing%20a%20Telling%20Post-Sept.%2011%20Political%20Dilemma%3A%20%27So%20Who%20Am%20I%3F%27&pqatl=google|dead-url=no}}</ref>，其中父親為{{Link-en|黎巴嫩裔美國人|Lebanese American}}，篤信[[馬龍尼禮教會|馬龍尼禮教會]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/darrellissa/info/?tab=page_info|title=Darrell Issa - About - Facebook|website=[[Facebook|Facebook]]|access-date=November 12, 2016|archive-date=2022-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220126173146/https://www.facebook.com/darrellissa/info/?tab=page_info|dead-url=no}}</ref>，母親則是[[德裔美國人|德裔美國人]]及{{Link-en|捷克裔美國人|Czech American}}（[[波西米亞人|波西米亞人]]）<ref name=WaPo2001>{{cite news|title=Transcript: Issa on Bomb Plot|issue=On Politics|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=December 12, 2001|author=eMediaMillWorks|access-date=September 7, 2013|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/onpolitics/transcripts/issa_text121201.html|quote=Following is the full transcript of a press conference held by Rep. Darrell Issa (R-Calif.) on the reported plot to bomb his California offices. Rep. Issa is the grandson of Lebanese immigrants. Other speakers: Rep. Tom Lantos (D-Calif.), Rep. Benjamin A. Gilman (R-N.Y.), Rep. Steve Israel (D-N.Y.), Rep. Gary L. Ackerman (D-N.Y.) and Rep. Jerrold Nadler (D-N.Y.).|archive-date=2012-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109002624/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/onpolitics/transcripts/issa_text121201.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/aponline/20011026/aponline175845_000.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203013459/http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/aponline/20011026/aponline175845_000.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=February 3, 2014|title=Rep. Issa: I Was Profiling Victim|work=Washingtonpost.com|date=October 26, 2001|access-date=September 30, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/16553/darrell-issa#.W-KZIHpKg0o|title=The Voter's Self Defense System|website=Vote Smart|language=en-US|access-date=November 7, 2018|archive-date=2019-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190814213937/https://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/16553/darrell-issa#.W-KZIHpKg0o|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2011/01/24/dont-look-back-ryan-lizza|title=Don't Look Back|magazine=The New Yorker|access-date=November 7, 2018|language=en-US|archive-date=2014-06-30|archive